策略競局                                


  	This course aims to provide a foundation for understanding interactions between people or firms in diverse fields such as economics, business, evolutionary biology, etc. It will cover basic concepts and techniques for analyzing interactions—games—in the framework of sequential and simultaneous moves, some specific classes of games, and a wide spectrum of applications. It will also emphasize practices via homework assignments and Lab sessions to enhance students’ comprehension in games of strategy.

課程教育目標 

A. 溝通能力B. 創新與解決問題能力D. 全球化視野 
課程基本素養與核心能力 

